I attempted training on audio and on spectrograms, using various frameworks (pytorch, fastai), with various ways of normalizing the data, but to no avail.

There is a chance there is a bug somewhere in my code - I checked the code over and over again and with high degree of confidence I believe there is no egregious bug that the results could be ascribed to.

In fact, I believe that the model is doing exactly what I ask of it - it is learning from the data I provide it. It is learning something, but I do not think it is learning to generalize. It fits to something in the provided train examples, but I don't think it fits to the calls we hope it will learn to recognize.

Our train data is not aligned with what we are asking of our model. Unfortunately, there is no silver bullet that will fix this for us. The only thing we can do is to modify our dataset. And unfortunately, that will require hand labeling.

But before we go invest a lot of energy into this effort, let us first evaluate if that indeed is the right path. We will not know for sure, but we can at least strive for some indication that indeed it might be the path to take.
